args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor the ＂Ageless Artifice＂ event, as well as the\nmain campaign through Chapter 11.
That makes this my fifth consecutive loss\nin the battle command simulation. As ever,\nI admire your composed judgment.

I'll win the next one, though. We were both
produced in the same period, and so we
possess equal capabilities. Anything you
can do, I can do as well.
You were the one who taught me so.\nIsn't that right...partner?
Ah...! That same weird dream again.\nThat was Eirene, but not as I know her.\nAt another time, in another place...
Gah, I'm so over this. Androids aren't\neven supposed to HAVE dreams. It's\nalways been like this for me, though.
Eirene... Just who in the world\nwas this so-called partner of yours?
Okie dokie, patrol complete! All enemy\nactivity in the surrounding area has been\nneutralized. We're good to keep moving.
Thank you, Finni. You two have made a\nworld of difference in our excursions.
Androids excel in searching out hostiles.\nEven then, Finni is particularly adept at it.

I'm just the right android for the job. I'm a
common foot soldier, really, so this kind of
grunt work is more up my alley than it is
for commander units like Eirene and Laxi.
I should be thanking YOU all for fixing my\nheart and welcoming us with open arms\nwhen we had nowhere else to go.
I aim to work off every bit of that\ndebt to you folks, so just sit back\nand lemme handle the heavy lifting!
Even now, you go above and beyond for us.
I must say, though, Finni—for an android,\nyou certainly are emotive. I sometimes\nforget you're mechanical at all.
Is Ex Machina's technological prowess to\ncredit for that, too?

Nah, not really. I was pretty much the odd
duck of the bunch back when I was with
them. Regular androids don't get
tilted nearly as easily as I do.

I wonder why that is. Maybe it's got
something to do with the fact that I'm
equipped with a heart even though I'm
your garden-variety mass-produced model?
True. Hearts are high-grade tech and\nnormally only installed in command\nunits. Finni is...special.
Hee hee. That must be why a grunt like me\nwas lucky enough to be assigned adjutant\nto a brilliant command unit like you!

I've been Eirene's rock ever since she
found me a thousand years back. And
I'm planning to be with her for a thousand
more!
Ha ha. You really love her, don't you?
You better believe it! Eirene's\nhappiness is my happiness!
Oh... Nothing. Part of my heart's kinda\ndamaged, that's all.

Sometimes it gives me those dizzy spells
you humanoids have. I've been powered
on for a looong time, so I figure it must
be normal system degradation.
(Still, it's weird. I feel like this has been\nhappening a lot more often—too often—\nsince we joined up with these folks.)
(And then there are the constant dreams.\nI hope it's not a bad omen or something.)

My episodes are similar to what humanoids call
daydreams. My consciousness dims, and then I
end up dozing off for a bit. It seemed like a pretty
harmless phenomenon, so I just rolled with it.

But...

I was nearly at my limit.
I just didn't know it yet.
During an operation carried out\nby Eirene's combat detachment\nNorth Grastaean Plains
Enemy signatures increasing. Fifty,\nsixty...now seventy! And still climbing!
Hah. Maybe humanoids would buckle here,\nbut we androids'll never be daunted by\nsuch paltry numbers! Let's go—full output!
There's plenty more where THAT came\nfrom! Hraaaah!
Don't push too far out, Finni!\nWork with the rest of the group!
It's fiiine! I'm about to put this whole\nthing to bed anyway. Assault on!\nArmed 72: Fastbreak—
There you are. I've been looking for you.\nThe war council is about to begin.
(Ugh. It's another one of these dreams.\nOf Eirene, but not as I've ever known her.\nWho's that she's with?)
All the leader units I was manufactured\nalongside should have convened by now.\nWhy are you lingering here?
I was watching birds. They bring me peace.\nI credit the engineer who built me with\nteaching me of their beauty.
(A unit built at the same time as Eirene?\nBut who?! I have no record of any such\nandroid!)
Mm. I suspect that notion was etched into\nyour circuits...your heart, that is.
Could be. Anyway, I apologize for holding\nyou up. I've seen enough birds for now.\nLet's be on our way, partner.
Eirene... I... Did I stop functioning?
Yes. Looks like there was a temporary\nshort in your circuits. We don't know what\ncaused it. I'm relieved that you're awake.
(What was that dream all about? Eirene\nwas calling someone else ＂Finni...＂)
Say, Eirene? When you found me,\nwas it...right after I was created?
What? Yes. Just after your heart started\nrunning, I requested that Ex Machina\nmake you my adjutant.
I'll never forget that day, no matter\nhow many thousands of years pass.
It WAS a thousand years ago, though,\nright? You're sure of that?
Never mind. Sorry. I think I'm just feeling\na little scrambled from that short.

(The dream I had today felt like it was
a little before the great war a thousand
years ago. That doesn't really mesh with
what Eirene said.)
(Is she hiding something from me?\nMaybe it's time I really started thinking\nabout what the dreams mean.)
(All right. I've decided: I'm gonna find out\nabout this other me...whoever she is!)
